{"tid":1107441,"cid":11,"subCid":0,"title":"莊文強《無雙》將重拍成南韓電影","createTime":"2019-04-15T09:06:12.000Z","updateTime":"2019-04-15T15:04:17.000Z","uid":134071,"like":4,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":16,"replies":[{"pid":"4d5b7a81bc8754bef120e59e6e6006895dbb4b83","tid":1107441,"uid":134071,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-04-15T09:06:12.000Z","msg":"莊文強的香港電影《無雙》將被重拍成南韓電影.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.koreanfilm.or.kr/eng/news/news.jsp?mode=VIEW&amp;seq=5121\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.koreanfilm.or.kr%2Feng%2Fnews%2Fnews.jsp%3Fmode%3DVIEW%26seq%3D5121&d=hmtFoPnP%2FIv5fOqUL3ZUaodddMXd0Scb%2F0m37zAf7q8%3D&h=07f03b76\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">http://www.koreanfilm.or.kr/eng/news/news.jsp?mode=VIEW&amp;seq=5121</a><br />\n<br />\nKorean Remake of PROJECT GUTENBERG in the Works<br />\nMar 25, 2019<br />\nWriter by Pierce Conran<br />\n<br />\nThe Chinese crime action drama Project Gutenberg is set to receive a Korean remake. As reported by Screen Daily during this year&rsquo;s Hong Kong International Film &amp; TV Market (FILMART), which takes place alongside the Hong Kong International Film Festival, Korean genre filmmaker KIM Hwi will direct the update, which will have a budget in the range of USD 12 to 15 million.<br />\n<br />\nThe Korean outfit NOORI PICTURES and Just Creative Studio (JCS), an affiliate of the Chinese company Bona Film Group, will jointly produce the project. The producer of the film will be KIM Jung-ah kathy, formerly the CEO of CJ Entertainment during the time it released KIM Jee-woon&rsquo;s The Good, The Bad, And The Weird (2008). NOORI&rsquo;s LEE Yong-ho and JCS&rsquo; Jeffrey CHAN will also join the film as executive producers.<br />\n<br />\nDirector KIM Hwi debuted with the serial killer The Neighbors in 2012 and later made the shamanism thriller The Chosen: Forbidden Cave, which served as the closing film of the Bucheon International Fantastic Film Festival (BIFAN) in 2015. KIM also came on board the period thriller The Tooth and the Nail (2017) at a late stage, joining director JUNG Sik on the film.<br />\n<br />\nThe original Protect Gutenberg, a Chinese-Hong Kong co-production featuring HK superstars CHOW Yun-fat and Aaron KWOK from director Felix CHONG, was a major hit in China last year, where it grossed almost USD 190 million. The film chronicles the hunt for a counterfeiting mastermind known as Painter."},{"pid":"ec524b1a86bc8e6099742ee50ff12436056b0a83","tid":1107441,"uid":37759,"like":30,"dislike":3,"score":27,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-04-15T09:10:02.000Z","msg":"正，港產the usual suspects比世界第二老翻大國攞去翻拍，成件事好有喜劇感<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"9a809c6ccb28807fd5abf38c1a63fbd79669dfe7","tid":1107441,"uid":134071,"like":15,"dislike":19,"score":-4,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-04-15T09:11:00.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>正，港產the usual suspects比世界第二老翻大國攞去翻拍，成件事好有喜劇感<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/no.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n係我心目中, 南韓而家係亞洲電影王國 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"f3bf231237aeac4ac2e35098b07961113a16a7bd","tid":1107441,"uid":24944,"like":13,"dislike":0,"score":13,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-04-15T09:12:30.000Z","msg":"香港人狂屌無雙劇本<br />\n但南泡又買<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/@.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"edc77e35108f95fcb663c950b35151ff0da8ec66","tid":1107441,"uid":228995,"like":15,"dislike":0,"score":15,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-04-15T09:17:10.000Z","msg":"正常<br />\n<br />\n發哥韓國都有market"},{"pid":"f3c8969cb29a7f2dad1d83a00ed0541540ab3401","tid":1107441,"uid":134071,"like":1,"dislike":1,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-04-15T09:17:29.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>香港人狂屌無雙劇本<br />\n但南泡又買<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/@.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n<br />\n南泡識欣賞 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" cl